    "updated_at": "2015-03-23T03:16:19Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Since it's a trait method, I think having `trait` in the name is better for trait-related public methods, so probably `hold_trait_notifications`. Since HasTraits is a very deep base class, I think its methods should be quite explicit about being trait-related, so as to avoid indication that they pertain to the terminal class's functionality.\n"
